{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And so my grandfather-- I remember in the-- wading into the Rhine River, and pulling out of it the scraps of the Torah that had been hacked to pieces, and the prayer books.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he gave them to me, and he said, here, take these.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I clutched them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I remember having this batch of wet parchment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he said, one day we'll put the pieces back together again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And of course, that one day was never to be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because thereafter, from the time my father left through Kristallnacht, the Nazis got very seriously involved with our family.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Because they wanted to harass us, to the point that my father would be shamed into coming back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And had he done that, I wouldn't be talking now either.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a real dilemma that the family faced.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother was interrogated every day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came for her to humiliate her and to try to get to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They kept asking, where is he?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother would say, I don't really know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my father would write to relatives in different cities, without writing for the first few months, to us in Oberwesel.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because he didn't want to endanger the family more than they were already endangered.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then people still traveled back and forth between Holland and Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So messages would come, telephone messages also.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SIGHS] So that my father then waited to go to Palestine, together with his cousin, Max Gottschalk.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They sat in a-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] special facility that had been prepared for Jews in transit, run by the Joint Distribution Committee, I think, awaiting for certificates which never arrived.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At which point, they began to process immigration to America.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
